sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User/Data Scientist
    participant Dashboard as ODH Dashboard
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Controller as Notebook Controller
    participant StatefulSet as StatefulSet<br/>(Notebook Pod)
    participant Service as Notebook Service<br/>80/TCP HTTP
    participant Gateway as Istio Gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant VirtualService as VirtualService<br/>80/TCP HTTP mTLS
    participant JupyterPod as Jupyter Pod<br/>8888/TCP HTTP

    rect rgb(220, 240, 255)
        note over User,StatefulSet: Flow 1: Notebook Creation
        User->>Dashboard: Create notebook via UI
        Dashboard->>K8sAPI: POST Notebook CR<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+<br/>User credentials
        K8sAPI-->>Controller: Watch Event<br/>Notebook CR created<br/>ServiceAccount
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Create StatefulSet<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount Token
        K8sAPI-->>StatefulSet: Deploy notebook pod
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Service<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount Token
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Create VirtualService (if USE_ISTIO=true)<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    end

    rect rgb(255, 240, 220)
        note over Controller,JupyterPod: Flow 2: Idle Notebook Culling (if ENABLE_CULLING=true)
        loop Every IDLENESS_CHECK_PERIOD (1 minute)
            Controller->>Service: GET /api/kernels<br/>HTTP/80
            Service->>JupyterPod: Forward request<br/>HTTP/8888
            JupyterPod-->>Service: Kernel activity status
            Service-->>Controller: Response
            Controller->>Service: GET /api/terminals<br/>HTTP/80
            Service->>JupyterPod: Forward request<br/>HTTP/8888
            JupyterPod-->>Service: Terminal activity status
            Service-->>Controller: Response
            alt Idle > CULL_IDLE_TIME (24h default)
                Controller->>K8sAPI: Update Notebook annotation<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount Token
                Controller->>K8sAPI: Scale StatefulSet to 0<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount Token
            end
        end
    end

    rect rgb(220, 255, 220)
        note over User,JupyterPod: Flow 3: User Accessing Notebook
        User->>Gateway: GET /notebook/{ns}/{name}/<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+<br/>OAuth/JWT
        Gateway->>VirtualService: Route request<br/>HTTP/80 mTLS (optional)<br/>Istio Policy
        VirtualService->>Service: Forward to notebook<br/>HTTP/80 mTLS (optional)
        Service->>JupyterPod: Proxy to container<br/>HTTP/8888
        JupyterPod-->>Service: Jupyter UI response
        Service-->>VirtualService: Response
        VirtualService-->>Gateway: Response
        Gateway-->>User: HTTPS response
    end
